<div id="review_529935748" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/529935748" />
    <a title="Karlene Browning" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1252975-karlene-browning"><img alt="Karlene Browning" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/529935748?book_show_action=true">Feb 08, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Karlene Browning" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Karlene Browning" href="/user/show/1252975-karlene-browning">Karlene Browning</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer529935748" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5695635956566051552">I have mixed feelings about this book, and the premise of the series. I think it&apos;s a fascinating story with some unique twists to the vampire legacy. The characters are strong, the plot captivating. The writing is pretty solid. Normally, this is exactly the kind of book I like to read and recommend.<br/><br/>The issue I have is I really don&apos;t like the paranormal mixing with my religion. Some of these vampires are LDS. I like that they&apos;re repentant and trying to make amends for their past. But...as I read,</span>
  <span id="freeText5695635956566051552" style="display:none">I have mixed feelings about this book, and the premise of the series. I think it's a fascinating story with some unique twists to the vampire legacy. The characters are strong, the plot captivating. The writing is pretty solid. Normally, this is exactly the kind of book I like to read and recommend.<br /><br />The issue I have is I really don't like the paranormal mixing with my religion. Some of these vampires are LDS. I like that they're repentant and trying to make amends for their past. But...as I read, that was a frequent personal irritant that pulled me out of the story. <br /><br />(As was the strong accent of the main character.)<br /><br />But putting that aside, this is a wonderful story of sin and redemption. It's a little gorey in parts, but hey, VAMPIRES. <br /><br />I recommend it if mixing religion and vampires is not personally offensive to you. (And yes, I will read the next book in the series.)</span>
  <a data-text-id="5695635956566051552" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


